Package: clade
Title: Agent-Based Evolutionary Simulation with Julia Backend
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "s.nakagawa@unsw.edu.au"),
    person("Vadim", "Bulitko", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Agent-based simulation of evolution and foraging ecology.
    Digital organisms carry heritable neural-network genomes (diploid or
    haploid) and one of six brain types: Bayesian neural network (default),
    multilayer perceptron, continuous-time RNN, gene regulatory network,
    transformer, or symbolic rule synthesis. Agents evolve over generations
    via natural selection on behaviour, life history, and cognition. The
    simulation runs entirely in Julia (via JuliaConnectoR), eliminating the
    per-tick R-backend boundary overhead and enabling runs of 100,000 agents.
    Provides MAP-Elites, CMA-ES (pure R, no external dependencies), and
    finite-difference gradient parameter search.
